cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper deals with convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and their performance in image classification tasks, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of a score function for CNNs, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The study of the dynamics of the score function during training also suggests a connection to neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the use of the score function in self-training methods for domain adaptation, which is related to natural language processing (cs.CL).
